  "body": "### Description\r\nWhen we fail to import a block because of an internal error, it doesn't trigger the invalid gossip logging so we currently don't get any record of the actual block content that was invalid.  We should always log the full block content (as hex encoded ssz) when block import fails with internal error so we can fully investigate.\r\n\r\nThis shouldn't depend on the setting to log invalid gossip being enabled and should only apply to internal errors, not blocks we reject for being invalid.",
